task.summary: Spells made during a game will now be available in match. Matches shutdown on server side if players quit game. Match loop is terminated when the match controller is destroyed
Fixed training room, match object shuts down when user leaves training room, so game play doesn't flicker

Player subproccess for spells are terminated when a match is exited, the game objects themselves should now be deleted when the game is exited. And when the server terminates it kills any such spell subproccess yay.
Fixing config file before it kade adds it to git ignore
I found a modal system I liked, and have used is to setup match rematch.
I have been working on the display of the basic spells to the user and have started working on code completion. Its awesome.

Integrated Tern, which does really cool code completion. However it will require a def file computerwizdef.json.js to be maintained in tandem to the Spellbook.js, which is shitty, I know but the payoff is very nice.
Commit, so kade can get what I have.
Commit, so kade can get what I have. I added ace-build to repo
Found why fps slows, dont understand but its the part of the hud that draws the numbers, I guess its really expensive the way im doing it.
